~Stay true to myself and not get caught up in what’s trending 
~Focus on my story telling 

Thank you all for being here and I hope you have a great New Year’s Eve!

Our hallway is wider than an average hallway but not wide enough to be very functional. The wall trim was the perfect addition!

How to preserve your hydrangeas🌿

You may have figured out by now that I love hydrangeas!  I was so excited to find a way to make our Annabelle hydrangeas last for years!! 

The key is to cut them when they’ve turned green but haven’t changed over to brown. First you will cut them to length for the vase your chose. Next, take all the leaves off the stem. Then, place the hydrangeas in a vase with no water and you’re done!  You can also spray them with hairspray which can make them last even longer.🤍
